    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pork mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-pepper-fajita-grain-bowl-with-chipotle-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p><p>Peel and chop most of your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Dice the <strong>remaining onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-pepper-fajita-grain-bowl-with-chipotle-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pepper strips</strong>,<strong> onion wedges</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and most of your <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan</p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a splash of <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong>, give everything a good mix up and cook, covered, for 7-8 min or until the veg is slightly softened and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> pork & pepper fajita mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-pepper-fajita-grain-bowl-with-chipotle-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your<strong> coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-pepper-fajita-grain-bowl-with-chipotle-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>diced onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>salsa</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-pepper-fajita-grain-bowl-with-chipotle-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>mayo</strong> to a separate small bowl with the <strong>remaining chipotle paste </strong>and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>chipotle mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-pepper-fajita-grain-bowl-with-chipotle-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>glorious grains </strong>to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2-3 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-pepper-fajita-grain-bowl-with-chipotle-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pork & pepper fajita mix</strong> over the <strong>warmed grains </strong>and spoon over the <strong>salsa</strong></p><p>Drizzle with the <strong>chipotle mayo</strong> and garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
